According to the FWC, widespread flowering is reported in the area around Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte and Collier – suggesting that the concentration is decreasing.
The bloom of algae spreads over a 210 - mile [210 km] coastline from northern Pinellas County to southern Lee County.
There are smaller blooms about 16 km from the coast of Hillsborough County, but there are fewer than last week.
Flowers have also been observed in Pasco County.
Medium concentrations in or at sea have been reported in Pinellas County during the last week, low to high sea concentrations in Hillsborough County, background concentration to high concentrations in Manatee County, background concentration to high concentrations in or in the sea off Sarasota County, background concentration to medium concentrations in Charlotte County, background concentration to high concentrations in or off Lee County and low concentrations in Collier County.
Breathing difficulties continue to be reported in Pinellas, Manatee, Sarasota, Lee and Collier.
No respiratory problems have been reported in northwestern Florida in the past week.
